The paper deals with the problem of detecting curvilinear structures in images, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV). The authors propose a deep learning approach that simultaneously performs segmentation and path classification, which involves training a neural network (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the benefits of this approach in terms of consistency across the processing pipeline, which is a common concern in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the authors use datasets of roads and neurons, which are commonly used in computer vision and neuroscience research, respectively (cs.NE, cs.IR).
